# Copy this file to app/.env and fill in ONE provider's values.
# app/.env is gitignored — your API key is never committed.

# ── Option A: Anthropic (production target per ADR) ──────────────────────────
LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# Model overrides (defaults match the ADR: Sonnet for convert, Haiku for edits)
# CONVERT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# EDIT_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
# JUDGE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# ── Option B: OpenRouter (cheap/free models — avoids burning Anthropic credits
#    on public/anonymous traffic) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT: LLM_PROVIDER must still say "openai" below. OpenRouter is reached
# via the OpenAI-compatible wire format, selected by OPENAI_BASE_URL — there is
# no separate "openrouter" provider value. Setting LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter here
# is silently treated as unrecognized and falls back to the anthropic path
# (see getProvider() in src/convert/client.ts), which will look for
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY instead and likely fail or hit the wrong provider.
# LLM_PROVIDER=openai
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# Model IDs on OpenRouter are ALWAYS "vendor/model" — a bare "gpt-4o-mini" will
# 400. Pick any slug from https://openrouter.ai/models, e.g.:
# CONVERT_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini
# EDIT_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini
# JUDGE_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini
#
# Two OpenRouter-specific optimizations are applied automatically whenever
# OPENAI_BASE_URL points at openrouter.ai — no extra config needed:
#   1. Every request is routed to the cheapest available provider for the
#      chosen model (provider.sort=price). OpenRouter's own default is only
#      price-*weighted* across providers, not guaranteed cheapest.
#   2. Optional: set *_MODEL_FALLBACKS (comma-separated model IDs) to give
#      OpenRouter an ordered fallback list — if the primary model errors,
#      rate-limits, or is unavailable, it automatically tries the next one
#      instead of failing the request. Recommended once you have public
#      traffic on a single cheap/free model, since those rate-limit first.
# CONVERT_MODEL_FALLBACKS=google/gemini-2.0-flash-001,meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct
# EDIT_MODEL_FALLBACKS=google/gemini-2.0-flash-001,meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct

# ── Option C: direct OpenAI (or another truly OpenAI-compatible endpoint) ────
# LLM_PROVIDER=openai
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/v1   # omit entirely for api.openai.com
# CONVERT_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# EDIT_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# JUDGE_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
